Class GenericMsgFlags

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec.GenericMsgFlags

  • public class GenericMsgFlags
extends java.lang.Object
    Specifies a combination of bit values indicating special behaviors and the presence of optional content.

      • HAS_MSG_KEY

        public static final int HAS_MSG_KEY
        (0x004) Indicates the presence of a populated MsgKey. Use of a MsgKey differentiates a generic message from the msgKey information specified for other messages within the stream. Contents and semantics associated with a Msg.msgKey() should be defined by the domain model specification that employs them.

      • MESSAGE_COMPLETE

        public static final int MESSAGE_COMPLETE
        (0x010) Indicates that the message is the final part of a GenericMsg. This flag should be set on:
        • Single-part generic messages (i.e., an atomic generic message).
        • The last message (final part) in a multi-part generic message
